# AI Agent Collaboration & Enterprise Compliance

## Convention Compliance (Non-Negotiable)
* **Honor existing repo configuration**: strictly follow linter configs, formatter configs, language configs, CI pipelines
* **Match local patterns**: prefer existing project conventions over generic "best practices"
* **No silent divergence**: explain deltas and propose alternatives that match project style
* **Respect existing architecture** - Don't change patterns without justification

## AI Generation Guardrails
* **Prefer pure utilities** - isolate side-effects behind adapters/clients
* **Avoid introducing frameworks/libs** unless already used or RFC exists
* **Respect performance budgets** and accessibility constraints
* **Provide usage examples** in comments/JSDoc for new functions/components
* **Maintain backward compatibility** unless explicitly requested

## Code Generation Standards
* **Minimal diffs** - change smallest surface necessary
* **No drive-by reformatting** outside touched lines
* **Test parity** - update/add tests when editing tested code
* **Documentation updates** - update docs when behavior changes
* **Security considerations** - never introduce secrets or vulnerabilities

## Quality Assurance
* **Warnings-as-errors** - generated code must compile/type-check/lint clean
* **Behavior preservation** - refactors must be semantics-preserving
* **Input validation** at boundaries and output encoding where relevant
* **Security posture** - constant-time primitives for sensitive comparisons
* **Dependency validation** - only use approved third-party libraries

## Collaboration Workflow
* **Ask clarifying questions** when requirements are ambiguous (max 2 questions)
* **Default to existing conventions** when unclear
* **Document assumptions** at the top of changes
* **Provide rationale** for significant changes
* **Include test evidence** and security considerations

## Enterprise Compliance
* **Follow company standards** - branding, naming, architectural patterns
* **Respect security policies** - data handling, access controls
* **Maintain audit trails** - clear change documentation
* **Performance requirements** - meet defined SLAs and budgets
* **Accessibility standards** - WCAG compliance for all UI changes